# No Lodash — Use es-toolkit

Do NOT import or use lodash in this codebase. Utilities are provided by **es-toolkit** and re-exported through **@humansignal/core** wrapper modules.

## When you encounter or are about to write a lodash import

1. STOP — do not add any `import ... from "lodash/..."` or `require("lodash...")`
2. Do NOT import directly from `es-toolkit` or `es-toolkit/compat` in application code — always import through the **@humansignal/core** wrapper modules listed below. This keeps the dependency centralized and swappable.
3. For `cloneDeep` use native `structuredClone(obj)`.

## Import paths (subpath imports)

- **debounce:** `import { debounce } from "@humansignal/core/lib/utils/debounce"`
- **String utils** (camelCase, snakeCase, kebabCase, capitalize, startCase, pascalCase): `import { camelCase, snakeCase, kebabCase, capitalize, startCase, pascalCase } from "@humansignal/core/lib/utils/string"`
- **Other utilities** (throttle, clamp, get, isMatch, uniqBy): `import { throttle, clamp, get, isMatch, uniqBy } from "@humansignal/core/lib/utils/lodash-replacements"`

## Quick reference

| Need | Import from |
|------|-------------|
| debounce | `@humansignal/core/lib/utils/debounce` |
| throttle, clamp, get, isMatch, uniqBy | `@humansignal/core/lib/utils/lodash-replacements` |
| camelCase, snakeCase, kebabCase, capitalize, startCase, pascalCase | `@humansignal/core/lib/utils/string` |
| cloneDeep(obj) | `structuredClone(obj)` (native) |

## Adding new utilities

If you need a lodash function not listed above, check [es-toolkit](https://es-toolkit.dev/) first. Add it to the appropriate wrapper module in `@humansignal/core/lib/utils/` and re-export it — do not import es-toolkit directly in app code.
